{
  "doc_id": "2690",
  "text": "Multiple daily dosing is known to decrease adherence [CITATION_1] . Warfarin is administered once daily, as is edoxaban but apixaban and dabigatran are each administered twice daily [25] [26] [27] . Rivaroxaban is given twice daily for the first 21 days of acute VTE treatment, followed by once daily dosing thereafter [28] . Routine INR monitoring can identify poor medication adherence during warfarin therapy as out-of-range INRs often result from warfarin non-adherence [CITATION_2] . In addition, repeated nonadherence to INR monitoring recommendations is easy to recognize and has been associated with increased thromboembolic risk and may therefore be a surrogate marker for non-adherence with taking warfarin doses as instructed [CITATION_3] . Warfarin has a long half-life and isolated subtherapeutic INR excursions do not appear to substantially increase the risk of thromboembolism [CITATION_4] .",
